cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on text detection in natural images. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of synthetic data, which could potentially fall under cs.IR (information retrieval) or cs.CL (computational linguistics) sub-categories.
